id: hac-jwim
title: Scheduled release candidate bump breaks hard-coded CLI version test
description: "Auto Release run 29894187971 correctly changed package.json and src/cli.ts from 2026.7.21-2 to the 2026.7.22 candidate, then release verification failed because tests/cli.test.ts asserted the old literal version."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[6]: automation,github-actions,regression,release,testing,versioning
created_at: "2026-07-23T04:55:09.217Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:20:11.808Z"
deadline: "2026-07-24T04:55:09.217Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T05:20:10.780Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: CLI composition verifies the Commander version against package.json rather than a stale literal; version.mjs check continues to enforce package.json and src/cli.ts parity; a dry-run candidate mutation proves the complete suite without publishing
definition_of_ready: Exact run logs identify one deterministic assertion failure
goal: Reliable conditional daily releases
objective: Remove stale version literals from release verification
value: Scheduled publication can complete after a date transition
impact: Restores automatic release availability
outcome: Candidate-aware version contract tests
why_now: The first scheduled production run after the prior delivery failed
parent: hac-suj3
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: 100
sprint: api-contracts-2026-07-23
release: 2026.7.23
reporter: github-actions
severity: high
environment: GitHub-hosted ubuntu-24.04 scheduled Auto Release at merged master 27187f3
repro_steps: "Run node scripts/release/auto-release.mjs --push after a date transition with unreleased commits; release:verify fails in tests/cli.test.ts after version apply"
resolution: CLI composition now derives its expected version from package.json while version.mjs retains parity enforcement across package.json and src/cli.ts.
expected_result: Candidate version mutation passes the entire release suite without stale assertions.
actual_result: Synthetic 2099.12.31 candidate passed 1209 tests 100 percent four-metric coverage and every release gate.
affected_version: 2026.7.21-2
fixed_version: 2026.7.23
component: release-automation
regression: true
customer_impact: Daily releases are blocked and GitHub issue #65 remains open
